1 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY Section 11, Chapter 366, O.S.L.
2 2024 (21 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section 20K), is amended to read as
3 follows:
4 Section 20K. A. Upon the effective date of this act On or
5 after January 1, 2026, Class B6 shall include the following criminal
6 offenses:
7 1. Striking, tormenting, mistreating, or administering a
8 nonpoisonous desensitizing substance to a police dog or police
9 horse, as provided for in subsection A of Section 649.1 of Title 21
10 of the Oklahoma Statutes this title;
11 2. Interfering with the lawful performance of a police dog or
12 police horse, as provided for in subsection B of Section 649.1 of
13 Title 21 of the Oklahoma Statutes this title;
14 3. Harming, torturing, injuring, disabling, or otherwise
15 mistreating or killing a service animal during the commission of a
16 misdemeanor or felony offense, as provided for in subsection D of
17 Section 649.3 of Title 21 of the Oklahoma Statutes this title;
18 4. Assault, battery, or assault and battery upon a Department
19 of Corrections employee by a person in the custody of the Department
20 of Corrections, as provided for in subsection A of Section 650.2 of
21 Title 21 of the Oklahoma Statutes this title;
22 5. Assault, battery, or assault and battery upon an employee of
23 a private prison contractor by a person incarcerated in an
24 institution operated by a private prison contractor, as provided for
Req. No. 3792 Page 2

1 in s ubsection B of Section 650.2 of Title 21 of the Oklahoma
2 Statutes this title;
3 6. Aggravated assault and battery upon a Department of Human
4 Services employee or contractor, as provided for in subsection C of
5 Section 650.2 of Title 21 of the Oklahoma Statutes this title;
6 7. Assault, battery, or assault and battery upon an employee of
7 the Office of Juvenile Affairs by a person in the custody of the
