11 B. Any person convicted of a Class B6 criminal offense set
12 forth in this section shall be punished in accordance with the
13 corresponding penalties provided for in the Oklahoma Statutes.
14 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 21 O.S. 2021, Section 51.1a, is
15 amended to read as follows:
16 Section 51.1a. Any person convicted of rape in the first
17 degree, forcible sodomy, lewd molestation, grooming, or sexual abuse
18 of a child after having been convicted of either rape in the first
19 degree, forcible sodomy, lewd molestation, grooming, or sexual abuse
20 of a child shall be sentenced to life without parole.
21 SECTION 3. AMENDATORY 21 O.S. 2021, Section 843.5, as
22 last amended by Section 8, Chapter 486, O.S.L. 2025 (21 O.S. Supp.
23 2025, Section 843.5), is amended to read as follows:
