1 j. offering or transporting a child for purposes of child
2 sex trafficking, as provided for in Section 1087 of
3 this title, and
4 k. child sex trafficking, as provided for in Section 1088
5 of this title;
6 5. “Enabling child abuse” means the causing, procuring, or
7 permitting of child abuse by a person responsible for a child’s
8 health, safety, or welfare;
9 6. “Enabling child neglect” means the causing, procuring, or
10 permitting of child neglect by a person responsible for a child’s
11 health, safety, or welfare;
12 7. “Enabling child sexual abuse” means the causing, procuring,
13 or permitting of child sexual abuse by a person responsible for a
14 child’s health, safety, or welfare;
15 8. “Enabling child sexual exploitation” means the causing,
16 procuring, or permitting of child sexual exploitation by a person
17 responsible for a child’s health, safety, or welfare;
18 9. “Grooming” means befriending and establishing an emotional
19 connection with, or providing lewd or sexually explicit material to,
20 a minor or a person responsible for the health, safety, or welfare
21 of a minor in order to lower the minor’s inhibitions with the intent
22 to engage or direct the minor in:
23 a. sexual intercourse,
24 b. a lewd act or proposal,
